Description: Virtual Reality Peripheral Network - library development files
 The Virtual-Reality Peripheral Network (VRPN) is a set of classes within a
 library and a set of servers that are designed to implement a network-
 transparent  interface between application programs and the set of physical
 devices (tracker, etc.) used in a virtual-reality (VR) system.
 .
 This package is a part of the VRPN suite.  For a full VRPN runtime and
 development installation, install the "vrpn" package.
 
