Package: vrpn-clients
Architecture: any
Section: net
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: Virtual Reality Peripheral Network - client applications
 The Virtual-Reality Peripheral Network (VRPN) is a set of classes within a
 library and a set of servers that are designed to implement a network-
 transparent  interface between application programs and the set of physical
 devices (tracker, etc.) used in a virtual-reality (VR) system.
 .
 The following applications (from the upstream "client_src") are included:
 .
   - add_vrpn_cookie
   - forcedevice_test_client
   - vrpn_ping
   - vrpn_print_devices
 .
 This package is a part of the VRPN suite.  For a full VRPN runtime and
 development installation, install the "vrpn" package.

Package: vrpn-server
Architecture: any
Section: net
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: Virtual Reality Peripheral Network - generic multi-function server
 The Virtual-Reality Peripheral Network (VRPN) is a set of classes within a
 library and a set of servers that are designed to implement a network-
 transparent  interface between application programs and the set of physical
 devices (tracker, etc.) used in a virtual-reality (VR) system.
 .
 This package provides a generalized server that can load most, but perhaps
 not all, server devices provided with this VRPN release.  It is configured
 using a vrpn.cfg file - examples can be found in
 /usr/share/docs/vrpn-server/ once you have installed the package.
 The package provides the following applications (upstream's "server_src"):
 .
   - vrpn_server
   - test_vrpn
 .
 This package is a part of the VRPN suite.  For a full VRPN runtime and
 development installation, install the "vrpn" package.

Package: python-vrpn
Architecture: any
Section: net
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, python
Description: Virtual Reality Peripheral Network - Python bindings
 The Virtual-Reality Peripheral Network (VRPN) is a set of classes within a
 library and a set of servers that are designed to implement a network-
 transparent  interface between application programs and the set of physical
 devices (tracker, etc.) used in a virtual-reality (VR) system.
 .
 This package provides a Python interface to the VRPN system, generated
 using SWIG and custom interface files.
 .
 This package is a part of the VRPN suite.  For a full VRPN runtime and
 development installation, install the "vrpn" package.
